values:
Hey all.

This will be my last post ever.  I really dont want a livejournal anymore, I dont have much time to update it.  Plus i kinda realized its not peoples bussiness what i do and stuff...i dunno anyways...lost of fun while it lasted...adios.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/11058.html

After cheering on Wednesday, Cenzie, Cecilee and I went to the store where my mommy works and tried to sell the rest of our Skowhegan Football cards.  We were sitting in the store eating pizza and talking when a Lake George Ranger came in.  Cecilee looked at him when he walked by and goes HEY ITS RANGER JOE! (Like on Full House) and when "ranger joe" walked back he came over to us and was like "by the way...Its ranger Bob." We were laughing so hard.  I didnt even think he heard Cec say that.  Man it was too funny.  We ended up going around Canaan and selling the cards to stores and stuff like that.  We walked up the roads near my house too, we sold all of them by the end of the day.  We then went to Derek's house to use the big trampoline to practice jumps on.  Erika was watching Little Erika and of corse little Erika had to come and join us.  Shes so cute.  We went back to my house and hung out.  Mechanzie left later on.  Cec slept over and went to the mall with Danica and I today.  Got some more stuff for school.  Cheering tomorrow from 7-12.  Then maybe the game in Bangor with Cecilee??? Still not sure yet.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/10856.html

Last night I had the weirdest dream! Really scary too, it was one of those dreams where you wake up, and fall back asleep, but the dream continues where it left off.  So there was like no escaping it. haha.  Anyways, Today Glen came over and hung out for a bit.  Later on my mom and I went to the store and I got to drive up my road yay! Haha Im mad because like everyone already has there permits! I am going in September, I really think that is a bad time to go...but I have to go sometime right?  But in September school just started, I have cheering, I have dance, just hope I can handle adding one more thing.  But oh well its only for 3 weeks so I will survive. 

Tomorrow I have cheering from 7-12 then Cecilee and Cenzie are coming over after to practice jumps.  So adios until then.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/10684.html

Today I had to get up and go to cheer practice at 7, my mom and I picked up Becka on the way.  Practice went good. We got our "Secret Football Players", I got some kid I dont even know.  Oh well, the whole thing sounds like fun, even though I still dont understand why WE have to buy stuff for a football player and give him something every day of Homecoming week.  I bet it wont even occur to the football players to do something nice back and at least give us a card or something to show they appreciate it.  Im not sure why I am complaining, so I will stop now.  After practice I went to Becka's house and hung out there until around 4ish.  Oodles and Noodles are the best Becka ;).  We finally got our TV straightened around today, which is good.  I still hate Sat. Dishes tho, much rather have regular cable, o well, once again I am complaining.  I am kinda excited for school to start now, I really wish the summer lasted longer tho.  I just want to go back to school to: Wear new clothes, start dance and cheering (officially), and to see everyone I have missed over the summer!  Well Im out for now.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/10331.html

Today I didnt do much.  Watched TV, house work, and practicing cheering was what my day consisted of.  Not too much excitment.  Tomorrow I have cheering practcice from 7-12, then after heading over to Becka's house for awhile to hang out.

Short Post, O well. Adios.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/10236.html

Today I got up and my dad was waiting for the Dish Network people to come and fix our TV.  I really hate sat. dishes, I would much rather have regular cable televison.  Ours is like always messing up and stuff, its quite annoying.  So they came and didnt do much, we still have like no channels and our TV is still messed up. Ohhh well.  So once my mom got out of work I went to Waterville with her.  Went into Maurices and got a new sweater and shirt, really cute.  I didnt get anything else, I wasnt in the "shopping mood".  Once I got home I watched some movie on one of the VERY FEW channels we have left on our televison.  It was Cash and Tango.  I usually am not like CRAZY about action movies, but I will still watch them, but this one was really really good.  Anyways who knows whats happening tomorrow.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/9778.html

Ok practice went well today.  I feel so bad for poor Jody, I know it killed her to have to sit out!  We went to Al's pizza for lunch, which was good since I was like starving.  Then over to Tire Ware House for the Car Wash.  We made a good amount of money I think, which is good.  We almost caused an accident tho!  We were on the side walk with signs and some guy on a motorcycle was staring at us, and a truck pulled out in front of him, but he didnt realize this because he was too busy looking at us.  Thank goodness he realized that truck pulled out before he smashed into it.  I had fun screaming at the cars and stuff, now lets hope I have a voice for tomorrow.  Once I came back home I slept for a bit, practice and the car wash wore me out.  I have no idea what I am doing tomorrow.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/9483.html

Today I got to sleep in...YESSSS.  I layed out in the sun for awhile since I figure we wont have too many sunny days left, got some reading done.  I went to the fair later on, had lots of fun. I ate so much tho! O well.

Tomorrow I have cheering from 7-12 and cheering pictures, then a Car Wash for cheering after that.  Should be fun.  

Adios
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/9381.html

Hey all
Got back from camping on Sunday afternoon.  Had lots of fun and lots of good times.  We went to different places like Clark's and the waterslides.  I never realized how mountainy New Hampshire is!  I know that sounds really dumb but oh well.  Cecilee's Poppy and Glenny liked to make fun of me for saying that.  But it is really pretty there.  The campsite had like a river and trails right in it and stuff so that was pretty cool.  Went swimming alot, leave it to me, I fell on a rock and cut my ankle like the first day we were there.  Im such a clutz!  Oh well, Cecilee decided to be weird and go on a skateboard with no shoes on...so obviously she fell and scrapped her foot.  She was fine until Glen looked at it and it looked like the bone was sticking out. Nice one Glenny.  I had lots of fun.

On Monday Savanna, Danica and I went to the fair after I had cheering practice.  Had fun.  I watched the Durby...that was one of the first times I have actually sat down and watched that.  I never thought that watching cars crash into each other would be so entertaining.  It was really cool though!  I guess I shouldnt judge things so quickly.  But anyways, after the fair Vanna and Danni came back to my place and slept over.  Vanna left pretty early in the morning so Danni and I hung out on Tuesday.

Today I had to get up to go to Cheering.  Went pretty good except poor Jody hurt her foot. I hope she gets better soon!  Glen came over for awhile after practice.  I am pretty tired tonight...Yes...I get to sleep-in in the morning, I dont have to watch Erika since she is going to Bible school for the week.

Adios for now.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/9035.html

Today I had to watch Erika for a while.  We decided today we were going to paint our nails and do all kinds of girly stuff like that.  So we went over to my house for awhile and did that.  Then I couldnt open a bottle of nail polish and decided to call Derek since we saw him pull into his house...and I asked him to come and open a bottle of nail polish for me...he wasnt too happy about that but he still did it.  Later on I went to the mall with Danica, her mom, and her foster sister.  Danica and I had quite the exciting day at the mall.  We went into Filenes and I bought a skirt and she bought a blazer, when we exited the store to go back into the mall...the alarm went off.  But no one stopped us so we just kept walking.  Then later when we were getting ready to meet her mom and sister out in the car (we had to walk through Filenes because we parked outside that store)  when we entered the store...the alarm went off again!  Once again...no one stopped us so we just kept walking.  And when we went through the final door and got out into the parking lot...the alarm went off AGAIN...so you can say that me and Danica were freaking out.  So we basically ran to the car and locked the doors once inside...just as soon as we did that...a security car flew around the parking lot...(by then Danica and I were in tears).  We had noooo clue why the alarm was going off!  We had slips for everything we bought!  It wasnt like we stole something!  So when Danica's mom and sister arrived...we told them what happened and her mom made us take out everything we bought at Filenes and check to see if a ink tag was left on it.  That whole time...the cashier didnt take off the ink tag when I payed for my skirt!  I was too scared to go back into the store and tell them what happened so Danica's Mommy was happy to do it for me.  Thank Goodness!  She came back and everything was fine...the Filenes people understood.  Lets just say Danica and I will be checking to see if the ink tag is left on our new clothes more often...that scared us soooo much, you dont even know!  But over all the mall was really fun, I always have a good time with Danni!  

This will be my last entry for awhile...I am going camping with Cecilee and her family until the 14th in New Hampshire.  Should be fun.  I just hate packing!  I always pack wayyy to much and I always foget a bunch of things.  So adios until then!
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/8774.html

Today was okay I guess.  Had to go and watch Erika until Derek got home.  Then I went back to my house and layed out by the pool and read...so maybe I could kinda get a tan?!?  Don't know if that worked or not.  Last night I had to explain like the whole movie Blow to Jaclyn.  She said she didn't like the movie...but then she only saw parts of it.  So she was asking all these questions about it and seemed pretty interested, for not liking the movie. LoL.  I thought that movie was really good.  I am usually not into drug movies and stuff but that was pretty good.  It made it more interesting knowing that the movie was based on a true story.  Plus it had Johnny Depp in it so...you know it had to be good.  Now Jaclyn got me thinking about it...so I wanna read a book on it.  I found one called- Blow: How a Small-Town Boy Made $100 Million with the Medellin Cocaine Cartel and Lost It All, by Bruce Porter and I think I wanna order it sometime.  Not that I am interested in learning about drugs but the whole concept of the movie was pretty interesting, so maybe I will try the book?  Okay enough of that.

Tomorrow I have to watch Erika again until Derek gets home, then I am off to the mall with Danica to start school shopping...man I havent even started yet!  I am so ready to go shop.

That hampster face I have is the cutest thing ever! I am not even full...I just love the hampster face! LoL.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/8642.html

I havent updated this for awhile...sorry!  On Sunday I went to the races with Cecilee.  AJ did awesome as usual!  Monday I ran errands with my mom then read alot.  I have been reading like constantly lately.  I read my whole book yesterday, it was really good. It was The Last Vampire By Christopher Pike.  Its the first book out of the Last Vampire series...I think there is six of them...but anyways Christopher Pike is like the best author in the world.  Then today I had to get up and go to the doctors for a physical...yuk.  I was really nervous cuz I hate the doctors and I had to have a guy this time.  I dont know why...He was the only one avaiable I guess.  Thank god I didnt have to take off any of my clothes...He just basically did stuff that required  me to actually show that I am capable of living haha.  He was like asking all these questions.  He was like ya now its time for the akward questions that the guy doctor has to ask.  Have u has sex?  Do u plan to? Blah Blah Blah...it was weird and i could tell that the doctor was soooo uncomfortable asking.  It was funny. But now i am at cecilee's house and we are going to head over to her Nanny and Poppy's house in a bit.  Adios for now.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/8370.html

Today I got up and walked across the street to watch Erika.  I fell back asleep and had really odd dreams...One of them was that there was this Island that was underwater and cats lived there...and I was taking a tour of the Island...underwater.  Really Weird. I think I had that dream because Erika's cat decided to sleep right on top of me. Then I woke up to Erika, 2 inches from my face telling me to wake up.  I love how she decides to get right up in my face.  We watched the Price is Right and ate breakfast as usual. GOD FOREBID THAT WE CHANGE OUR MORNING RITUAL.  We heard a dirtbike outside and thought it was Jake so I told Erika to go answer the door cuz I didnt wanna deal with him since he doesnt like me or whatever.  It turned out to be Rachel so I had to run to the door to say Hi to her.  What a nice babysitter I am, I tell the kid to go answer the door...for all we know it could be a masked murdurer or a kidnapper or something...but we got something worse...RACHEL! haha jk rachel. Then her friend Brittany called and wanted her to come over to play.  Everything was all worked out so that Erika was going to get picked up and go over there...which was fine with me cuz i got to go home lol.  So I went home and slept for a bit since I was sooo tired, then mom came home and wanted me to go shopping with her.  So we went to Fairfield and went out to eat at the Purple Cow.  We decided to eat before going shopping cuz we would buy everything in sight if we went grocery shopping while hungry haha.  We went and did that and I saw Mr. Fitz the best teacher in the world into Walmart.  He looks so good and I hope he feels better!  It was nice to see him, I miss him alot.  Weird to think that my dad had him as a teacher and I did too lol.  I came home and watched the Wedding Planner for awhile, I love that movie!  Went online for a bit and now I am planning on going to sleep soon. Yay I dont have to get up in the morning!
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/7965.html

Cecilee came over on Tuesday and we were in a wicked hyper mood...we were laughing at everything.  We do that alot. We get into these queer moods and annoy the crap out of anyone who is around us...good thing we were alone this time.  Anyways we hung out and we went to Angelos Pizza with my mom.  The next day we had to get up at the crack of dawn and go to cheering practice.  That went good. I went to the libary and got new books to read since I havent read a thing since school got out. Bad me.  I got this really good book and read it all yesterday, I finally finished it at like 2 in the morning.  I do that often if I get a really good book, I cant put it down. Christopher Pike is like the best author ever. Our whole road lost power for a bit because of that HUGE thunderstorm...but when the power cam back on...the phones didnt so I couldnt go online all last night and justa bout died.  The phones finally come back on this morning. Then today I had to go over to Erikas at 7:30 to watch her...I went back to sleep as soon as I walked through the door,  we didnt get up until 11 today and I had some funky dreams lol.  I had to leave early to go to gymnastics so Big Erika came to watch Little Erika for me.  Gymnastics went good too.  I feel like I am doing alot better on my backhandspring...hopefully will have that soon all by myself...god I sound like a little kid...ALL BY MYSELF.  Anyways I have to watch Erika again tomorrow...should be fun...maybe?
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/7842.html

I didnt do much today, woke up this morning to my mom vaccuming the house at 8 in the morning, but I went back to sleep.  Got up and did dishes :(  and did a work out video.  Now I gotta go outside and run..yuk

Tomorrow I have to watch Erika until gymnastics at 1:30, then after gymnastics Cecilee is sleeping over and then we have cheering in the morning.

I had the most stupid dream ever that it was my dance recital and everyone was screwing up really bad, Jessica fell flat on her face, Nicole kept coming in on the wrong parts, people were just standing there like weirdos and I got stuck in the curtain and couldnt do anything.  Why am I dreaming about dance recital when that was in May?!? Lol weird.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/7374.html

Havent done much for the last couple days.  Today I pretty much slept until I could sleep no more, then layed out for awhile so I could maybe get some color...but didnt do much good.  Then I watched Dirty Dancing for the kajillionth time...but thats okay cuz it is just about the best movie ever.  Then I went outside for a bit to practice jumps and crap for cheering...then I decided that I needed to go and run...but I didnt want to run on the road that my mom and I usually walk on because she was not home and I didnt dare to go alone. Just my luck someone would kidnap me.  So I ran 10 laps around my house and pool and stuff. It sucked..but oh well gotta do it right?
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/6957.html

The Wedding Crashers was a really funny movie, some nudity but it was still funny.  After Danica and I went to see that I went back to her house and slept over.  I had to sleep in her brother's room.  Her brother is in a training corse thing for the army...so he doesnt live with them, but he recently visited them...with his girlfriend, so I was kinda freaked out to sleep in that bed man.  I didnt move around that much lol.  Anyways we told each other that the first one to wake up had to wake up the other one who was still sleeping.  So this morning I woke up to a cell phone right near my face...ringing and ringing over and over again.  What a weirdo.  So we hung out for the day and went swimming at her aunt's house. Then I got home, ate a BLT, and didnt do alot.  I have cheering tomorrow at 7 in the morning, its gunna suck getting up. I am kinda in a bad mood right now...for no reason, just feel like it, people make me mad really easy.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/6882.html

Today I woke up at 1 in the afternoon...seriously I am the laziest person ever! haha O well.  Tonight I am going to the movies with Danica for a bit.  I am still not sure what we are seeing lol...eather The Wedding Crashers or Charlie and the Chocolate Factory again...believe me I dont mind seeing that one again!
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/6645.html

Today I woke up at like 12:30 cuz the phone kept ringing.  So whatever I guess it was about time that I got my lazy butt out of bed.  Then I went online for a bit, watched TV etc.  Then Glenny called to say that he was heading over to my house.  I didnt mind at all...to bad i was still in my PJ's...oh well.  So we hung out for a bit and watched Pirates of the Caribbean...since he has NEVER SEEN THAT MOVIE.  I couldnt believe that!  After he left I helped Mommy make Dinner and watched another Shark special, I <3 Sharks now, dont ask...

Adios for now...
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/6169.html

I woke up only to hear Erika's squeeky, little, annoying voice at 7 in the morning...god help me.  My mom has had to watch her for the past week and a half just for like a half hour in the morning, then she brings her to day camp for the day, so we dont have to watch her! haha.  Then I woke back up at like 8 in a panick because my FIRE ALARM was going off!  This must have been the funniest sight in the world...here I am half asleep trying to figure out why a alarm would be going off..finally when I realized it was a fire alarm I started to panick, and I looked all over for some huge flame of fire...and nothing...I think the battery was low so thats why it did that.  So then I woke up AGAIN to my mom telling me to go sleep in her room cuz the cable guy was here and she didnt really want me snoring away while hes working on the TV in my room...which was probley a good idea.  I had gymnastics today, so my mom brought Cenzie, Cec and I to that...only to find Britny and Brandy waiting outside cuz the instructor did show up yet.  We waited...and waited...and no one showed up after 20 minutes so we left. We went to Walmart then we dropped off Cecilee at Brett's house/shop thinger, and then Cenzie and I went and got icecream, Cenzie pointed out something...isnt it weird how we get icecream...on a cone..and lick it off with out tongues?!?  That is so weird to me.  Anyways...we headed back home and my mom's car decided to be weird and start stalling and stuff..i found it hilarious..but apparently she didnt.  Then I decided to watch specials on TV about Sharks...I like sharks now...they are freaky but kinda cool. 

Maria is awesome! Miss ya!
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/6077.html

Yesterday after getting home from the dog show, I called Jaclyn since my mom told me she called.  We made plans to go to the movies and for her to stay over after.  We went to go see Charlie and the Chocolate Factory finally!  It seriously is like the best movie in the world.  I loved it.  I liked it more than the original movie.  Johnny Depp is seriously the best actor on the planet, no questions asked.  Not only is he hott, but he can like transform into anything for a movie.  Its so cool.  Jaclyn and I made sure that we bought a bunch of junk to eat at the movies.  After the movie we went back to my house and hung out, we watched the Sponge-Bob movie until we fell asleep.  We had to bring Jaclyn home before 11 cuz her daddy was picking her up to go to his house in Portland.  So now I am eating pancakes.  I dont know what I want to do today...
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/5878.html

Last night I went to Cecilee's cuz we all planned to go and see Charlie and the Chocolate Factory but little did we know that it was sold out, so we wanted to go to the 9:15 show but we had no one to watch baby Connor, so we rented movies instead.  So Cecilee, Glenny, Brett, AJ and I all went back to her house and watched movies all night, even though we had to get up early the next morning to go to AJ's dog show thinger.  So we got up extra early and got ready for that.  AJ got a new little American Bulldog puppy and they entered him in this contest and he got 1st place, he was so adorable.  I am soo hot right now, I wish our pool was cleaned so I could go swim, but you know, tough luck for me.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/5510.html

Just got back from cheer camp yesterday, it was ALOT of work but it was still alot of fun.  Im all brused up from doing the stunts, but thats okay. The days seemed sooooo long there, cuz we were up at like 6 getting ready and practicing and going to classes until 9 at night.  But the food, omg the food was so good there LoL.  It was good to get to know the other people on the squad, had some fun times.  We got a spirit stick every night, so we all were really happy about that.  Cecilee, Cocoa, Britny, Brandy and Jody made All American, so I was very proud of them for doing that.  I am glad to be home though.  CHARLIE AND THE CHOCOLATE FACTORY TONIGHT!!! YESSSSSS...I have been waiting to see this flipping movie for like ever!  So should be fun.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/5336.html

This will be my last entry until the end of the week since I am leaving for cheer camp tomorrow morning.  Today will mostly consist of getting ready for camp packing, laundry etc.  I had the weirdest dream the other night that my grandma bought a FireBird, and we were testing it out.  That is extremely scary since she doesnt have her licence...hmmmm weird.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/5040.html

I have been at home for wayyyyy to long.  I cant stay at my house for a long time with out dying of complete bordom.  I like being at home, but man after a couple of days it gets boriiinnngggg.  Today I went to town with my mommmy.  We had to go get Cheering Spankies since camp is coming up soon, going to camp with out spankies would not be a good thing.  Then we went and ate at the Purple Cow in Fairfield where this little kid beside us kept dropping toast and staring at us while we were eating. It was creepy.  Anyways then we went and got groceries etc. etc.  Now I am back at home, what to do, what to do?
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/4799.html

Jakiebabe came over the other day.  We ate junk and gained 41546 pounds together, o well.  We watched Meet the Fockers and Diary of a mad black woman.  That was a really good movie man, it was sad.  I was kinda in a bad mood for the rest of the night just because someone stressed me out majorly.  It was fun hanging with Jaclyn for a change.  Gotta do it sometime soon again.  Yesterday, my mom and I had to run to Newport for cheering crap.  Cheer camp is like next week and I dont have half the stuff I need. O well. Should be fun.  I feel so lazy today its not even funny.  I swear, when i woke up today I heard someone talking to like a dog or something.  All i heard was COME ON PAUL, YOU CAN DO IT, COME HERE PAUL.  I was so confused man, no one else was home..and we dont have a pet named Paul lol.  Maybe I was still dreaming I dunno.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/4395.html

Today I got to sleep...yessssssssss. I love sleeping, so I got up around noon and watched TV while eating breakfast.  Mom called me and said she was going to pick me up at 2:00 to go to Pittsfield with her because she had a doctors appointment.  So I sat in the car while she went into the doctors office..I apparently do not know how to work a freakin air conditioner because I THOUGHT it was on..but I guess not since I was sitting there sweating to death.  She came out about a zillion hours later..after I died of heat stroke.  We went to Subway and the Pool Place since our pool was kinda icky looking.  Then on our way back home I saw the most nasty thing ever.  Seriously, I have never seen anything more gross and sad.  A poor little cat got run over, and it was still moving.  It was so sad.  I almost cried.  This is why we dont let our cats out of our house, because people who cant drive, run over little kittys.  Anyways, I went back home and hung out and watched National Treasure with my dad.  Thats a cool movie.  Tomorrow I have cheering.
http://xodes08xo.livejournal.com/4295.html

Im not in the greatest mood right now. I dont know why, I feel like being in a bad mood so I am going to be.  I went to Cecilee's house on Saturday even though she was not home, she was getting back from the fireworks with Brett I guess and got home late.  I ate with her family and watched apart of a baseball game with them, her step-dad makes me laugh.  Anyways I went in her room and watched the movie Cry-Baby on TV.  It was all quiet and I heard a huge bang and Cecilee's laugh, she fell in the hallway while coming in her room...nice one.  So anyways we went to the races on Sunday, A.J. did awesome as always.  We went back to her house and slept.  Today we got up and went to her Auntie's house cuz it is Glenny's birthday on tuesday.  So we went and hung out there for awhile, it was really fun.  Her step-dad took Glenny, Cecilee and I to the movies, and we saw War of the Worlds, it was pretty good.  We then met up with some more of her family at the fireworks in Skowhegan.
